# Fix Backend Startup Errors & Enable Login

The backend has 5 failing services preventing login. This plan fixes each root cause with targeted code changes, then rebuilds everything.

## Root Cause Analysis

| # | Service | Root Cause | Fix Type |
|---|---------|-----------|----------|
| 1 | **Identity** | `spring.flyway.enabled: false` in `application.yml` prevents Flyway from creating the `saep_identity` schema, so Hibernate DDL fails | Config fix |
| 2 | **Communication** | Two `@Service` classes both named `idempotencyService` — one from `saep-outbox-starter` and one local — cause a `ConflictingBeanDefinitionException` | Rename bean |
| 3 | **Governance** | `GenericProposalValidator` has `@Component` **and** is manually instantiated via `@Bean` methods in `ValidatorConfig`. Spring also tries to auto-create it via component scan, but can't inject the `String type` constructor param | Remove `@Component` |
| 4 | **Audit** | Uses a stale `saep-common` JAR where `SaepSecurityConfig` had a constructor requiring `JwtAuthenticationFilter`. Current source is fixed, just needs rebuild | Rebuild only |
| 5 | **Marketplace** | Missing JAR — service was never compiled | Rebuild only |
| 6 | **Gateway** | Fails because Identity service (port 3002) isn't up. Fixing Identity fixes Gateway | Cascading fix |

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Identity Service — Enable Flyway Schema Creation

#### [MODIFY] [application.yml](file:///d:/College/Projects/Kyrti-Stop-managing-prompts.-Start-leading-an-enterprise/saep-identity/src/main/resources/application.yml)

Change `spring.flyway.enabled` from `false` to `true` and add `create-schemas: true` so Flyway creates the `saep_identity` schema before Hibernate attempts DDL:

```diff
   flyway:
-    enabled: false
+    enabled: true
     baseline-on-migrate: true
+    create-schemas: true
+    schemas: saep_identity
+    default-schema: saep_identity
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The `application.properties` already has `spring.flyway.create-schemas=true` and `spring.flyway.schemas=saep_identity`, but the `.yml` file explicitly sets `enabled: false` which takes precedence since both are loaded. Enabling it in the yml and adding the schema config ensures Flyway creates the schema on startup.

