### 2. Communication Service — Resolve Bean Name Conflict

#### [MODIFY] [IdempotencyService.java](file:///d:/College/Projects/Kyrti-Stop-managing-prompts.-Start-leading-an-enterprise/services/saep-parent/saep-communication/src/main/java/com/saep/communication/service/IdempotencyService.java)

Give the communication service's `IdempotencyService` a unique bean name to avoid conflicting with the outbox starter's bean:

```diff
-@Service
+@Service("communicationIdempotencyService")
 @RequiredArgsConstructor
 public class IdempotencyService {
```

This resolves the `ConflictingBeanDefinitionException` since both beans are named `idempotencyService` by default.

---

### 3. Governance Service — Remove @Component from GenericProposalValidator

#### [MODIFY] [GenericProposalValidator.java](file:///d:/College/Projects/Kyrti-Stop-managing-prompts.-Start-leading-an-enterprise/services/saep-parent/saep-governance/src/main/java/com/saep/governance/validation/GenericProposalValidator.java)

Remove `@Component` since instances are already created via `@Bean` methods in `ValidatorConfig`:

```diff
 package com.saep.governance.validation;
 
 import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;
-import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;
 
-@Component
 public class GenericProposalValidator implements ProposalPayloadValidator {
```

The `@Component` annotation causes Spring to try creating an additional instance via component scan, auto-wiring the `String type` constructor param — which fails because there's no `String` bean. Removing it ensures only the explicitly configured `@Bean` instances from `ValidatorConfig` are used.

---

### 4. Full Maven Rebuild

After the code fixes, run a full Maven build to rebuild all modules (including Audit and Marketplace):

```bash
mvn clean package -DskipTests
```

This resolves:
- **Audit**: Gets the updated `saep-common` JAR (current `SaepSecurityConfig` no longer requires `JwtAuthenticationFilter` constructor param)
- **Marketplace**: Builds the missing JAR

